\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
Visitor / Unregistered User:
\emph default
 a person who installed the SafeStreets application but never registered
 to the service.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

He can only view a brief explaination of the application's functions and
 proceed with the registration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
User / Registered User
\emph default
: a person who executed the whole registration procedure, providing necessary
 information and confirming its registration by following the link in a
 confirmation email.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

He can log to his user account though the application to access all of the
 functionalities it provides to normal users without particular permissions.
 This means he can send a violation 
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Manage the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

violation
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 definition carefully
\end_layout

\end_inset

 and view its previous violations, view information on streets with the
 most violations.
 He can't view violations submitted by other users.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
Administrator:
\emph default
 SafeStreets employee whose role is to manually manage user accounts (for
 example by assigning or removing roles and permissions)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\emph on
Officers / Authority:
\emph default
 police officer or other type of municipality employee involved with SafeStreets
' activity.
 He can indipendently sign up for an account and request its Officer permissions
 to be granted aftwerwards by an Administrator.
 Alternatively, the municipality can ask Safestreets to make an Administrator
 create its account with relevant permissions already set.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

He can everything a Registered Users is allowed to do, and can search violations
 sent by all users.
 
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Can view sender data?
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

